<HEADLINE> Maradona Talks with Spanish club, newspaper says </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, July 27 (Xinhua) -- Argentine soccer idol Diego
Maradona talked with Spanish second division club about his
possibility to coach in the humble side, said the headline of
Spanish sports daily Marca on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The newspaper said Maradona could join Badajoz as player-coach
next season after the player's manager Guillermo Coppola
negotiated with the club. But no agreement had been reached
between Coppola and Badajoz's owner Argentine comic Mauricio
Tinelli.
</P>
<P>
Earlier this year, Maradona was reported to join an Argentine
second division team, while during the France 98 World Cup, he was
reported to negotiate with an English team. 
</P>
</TEXT>
