<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Singapore Needs to Reexamine Strategy: Official </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, July 27 (Xinhua) -- Singapore Deputy Prime Minister
Lee Hsien Long has said his country needs to thoroughly re-examine
its strategy and competitiveness so as to tide over the current
economic difficulties.
</P>
<P>
During a meeting with unionists Monday, he said Singapore must
change policies where necessary and strengthen its competitiveness
in order to weather the current economic storm and prosper once
again.
</P>
<P>
As the whole country is facing a real test resulting from
regional economic crisis, he said, there is a need to change the
mindset of workers despite the country has ample reserves, a sound
economy and good tripartite relations.
</P>
<P>
"Workers not only need skills but also must be prepared to take
on shift duties," he said.
</P>
<P>
Otherwise, many well paying jobs would continue to go to
skilled foreign workers, he said.
</P>
<P>
He urged the unionists to use the crisis as a chance to bond a
new generation of Singapore. 
</P>
</TEXT>
