<HEADLINE> India's Mig-21 Fighter Crashes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, July 27 (Xinhua) -- An Indian Mig-21 fighter plane
crashed on Monday in Assam State's Dibrugarh district, official
sources said.
</P>
<P>
Details of the accident were not immediately available. The
pilot and a trainer bailed out to safety with minor injuries, the
sources said.
</P>
<P>
The mishap took place at Balijan tea estate in Assam State and
it was yet to be known the reason behind the accident. 
