<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Japanese Ship Fire off UAE Under Investigation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABU DHABI, July 27 (Xinhua) -- A special committee on Monday
began to investigate the cause of a fire on a Japanese cargo ship
at Khaled seaport in the al-Sharja Emirate of the United Arab
Emirates.
</P>
<P>
The committee will also assess the losses caused by the fire.
</P>
<P>
The committee includes al-Sharja Emirate's border and coast
guards, officials of civil defense, insurance companies, owner of
the ship and the port department.
</P>
<P>
The ship carrying 3,000 new and second-hand cars caught fire
Thursday night when the vehicles were being unloaded.
</P>
<P>
The border and coast guard department has ruled out the
possibility of crime in the fire incident.
</P>
<P>
In a statement issued on Sunday, the department director, Saud
Abdul Aziz, said the fire was most likely triggered by an electric
spark in one of the cars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
