<HEADLINE> Chinese Ministry Asks All Departments To Help With Flood Relief </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 27 (Xinhua) -- China's Water Resources Ministry
today asked government department to do everything they can in the
flood-relief effort.
</P>
<P>
It says that this is the most dangerous flooding in the Yangtze
River Valley since 1954. The water level in Wuhan, on the middle
reaches, was 28.8 m at 8:00 pm today, 2.5 m above the danger mark,
according to the latest report.
</P>
<P>
Water levels on Dongting and Boyang lakes, which are catch
basins for much of the river's water, are also exceeding record
levels and continuing to climb.
</P>
<P>
The Nenjiang River in Heilongjiang Province is also suffering,
according to the Ministry and it said that hydrology departments
should monitor all changes in water levels, and people in charge of
water conservation areas at reservoirs, dikes, and dams should try
to do their best. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
