<HEADLINE> DPRK Marks 45th Anniversary of the National Liberation War </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PYONGYANG, July, 27 (Xinhua) -- The Democratic People's
Republic of Korea (DPRK) is appreciative of the aid provided by
the Chinese people in material and manpower during the 1950s
national liberation war, Kim Yong Chun, chief of the general staff
of the People's Armed Forces, said Monday.
</P>
<P>
Kim's words came at a celebration marking the 45th anniversary
of the national liberation war, also known as the Korean War,
which witnessed the DPRK people, joined by the Chinese People's
Volunteers (CPV), preventing the armed invasion by the United
States into the DPRK in the 1950s.
</P>
<P>
Vice-President Pak Sung Chul and Vice-Premier and Minister of
Foreign Affairs Kim Yong Nam joined government and military
leaders in the celebration.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Ambassador to the DPRK Wan Yongxiang and other foreign
diplomats were also present at the assembly.
</P>
<P>
DPRK party and government Leaders laid wreaths at the
Korea-China Friendship Tower on Monday morning in memory of the
CPVs who died in the war. 
</P>
</TEXT>
