<HEADLINE> 1stadd: Israeli Military Plane Crashes, Airmen Safe </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, July 27 (Xinhua) -- An Israeli military plane
crashed during training Monday near the West Bank town of Hebron
but the two airmen baled out safely, Israel Radio reported.
</P>
<P>
The plane, an A-4 Skyhawk jet fighter, crashed after going into
a dive as part of the training. Both the pilot and navigator were
said to be slightly injured and were picked up to hospital for a
routine check-up, the radio said.
</P>
<P>
It was the third crash of Israeli military planes this
year. Four airmen were killed in two separate accidents in
March. 
