<HEADLINE> Chinese Knowhow May Help Take Lean Out Of Tower Of Pisa </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, July 27 (Xinhua) -- A building engineer from China
says that the technology he has developed could be useful therapy
for helping Pisa's leaning tower.
</P>
<P>
The specialist, Cao Shizhong, made the announcement today as he
left for a 20-day visit to Italy at the invitation of the
Associazione Italia-Cina (Italy-China Association).
</P>
<P>
The association has arranged meetings with local authorities to
discuss repair work using Cao's patented methods for helping the
famous Italian building that he has been working on since the
1960s and which he says has been his dream.
</P>
<P>
Cao wrote to the Italians about saving the tower when he
thought that he'd got the answer and said that all methods used
until now had been wrong, including putting lead casts in the
basement.
</P>
<P>
To date, he has used his technology to take the lean out of 80
ancient towers and buildings throughout China, with a success rate
of 100 percent. 
</P>
