<BODY>
<HEADLINE> EU to Spend 48.6 Million ECU on Environment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, July 27 (Xinhua) -- The European Commission is going
to spend 48.6 million ECU (53.4 million U.S. dollars) this year on
environment-related projects.
</P>
<P>
The commission, the executive body of the 15-nation European
Union, said on Monday that it will use the fund for nature
conservation and environment demonstration projects.
</P>
<P>
Out of the 192 applications for nature conservation funds, the
commission chose 85 projects for this year's funding, 25 projects
more than last year.
</P>
<P>
Officials said that the type of projects has shifted in the
last three years from bird protection to the protection of habitat
types and species.
</P>
<P>
The commission also received 634 demonstration applications and
sorted out 116 projects for the fund.
</P>
<P>
The demonstration projects focus on waste treatment and
recycling, water issues, land use planning, air-related problems
and noise pollution.
</P>
<P>
The fund will be managed by the commission's financial
instrument, LIFE, which provides aid for the environment
throughout the European Union and in bordering regions as well.
</P>
<P>
The objective of LIFE is to contribute to the development and
implementation of the EU environmental policy by financing
specific environmental actions. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
