<HEADLINE> Major News Items in Leading U.S. Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, July 27 (Xinhua) -- The following are major news
items in leading U.S. newspapers on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The Washington Post:
</P>
<P>
-- AT&AMP;T and British Telecom, two of the world's oldest and
largest telephone companies will join their vast international
operations into a global venture that will sell 10 billion
U.S. dollars a year of telephone, internet and data services to
big corporate customers around the globe.
</P>
<P>
-- Millions of Cambodians went to the polls on Sunday to vote
in a national election that they hoped might resolve the country's
political stalemate and end a quarter-century of almost continuous
conflict.
</P>
<P>
The New York Times:
</P>
<P>
-- Keizo Obuchi, the man in line to be Japan's next prime
