</P>
<P>
-- Bell Atlantic Corp. and GTE Corp. have been holding
high-level talks about a possible merger that could be valued at
between 52.5 billion and 55 billion dollars. The deal would be the
latest in a series of mergers reshaping telecommunications.
</P>
<P>
-- A deeply critical assessment of Malaysia's economic
leadership and outlook by Moody's Investors Service Inc. has
forced the government to temporarily shelve a much-needed
sovereign bond issue aimed at reviving the debt-ridden economy.
</P>
