<HEADLINE> EU Launches Investigation on Mobile Phone Service Prices </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, July 27 (Xinhua) -- The European Commission announced
on Monday an in-depth investigation into mobile phone service
prices in eight member states.
</P>
<P>
Stefan Rating, spokesman for European Competition Commissioner
Karel van Miert, told the press that it was not an infringement
procedure but only an investigation.
</P>
<P>
He said the commission wants to suggest a benchmark for
cost-effectiveness for mobile phone services after the
investigation.
</P>
<P>
The commission, the executive body of the 15-nation European
Union (EU), decided on the investigation after conducting an
inquiry into high mobile communications prices in all member
states.
</P>
<P>
Some 100 questionnaires sent out earlier this year indicated
the possibility of excessive or discriminatory prices.
</P>
<P>
The eight member states involved are Belgium, Ireland, Britain,
Austria, Spain, the Netherlands, Italy and Germany. 
</P>
