<HEADLINE> Protecting Yangtze River's Ecology </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 27 (Xinhua) -- Fifteen college students left
Beijing today for the Hoh Xil Area in northwest China's Qinghai
Province to work for the environment near the source of the
Yangtze River, the State Environmental Protection Administration
reports.
</P>
<P>
The students were recruited from more than a dozen colleges in
the cities of Beijing, Chengdu, and Guangzhou, and will
participate in building an environmental protection station in Hoh
Xil and learn more about the environment at the source of the
Yangtze.
</P>
<P>
The first environmental protection station in the area was
built at 4,600 meters above sea level last September, but it
lacked funds and equipment to halt illegal hunting and carry out
studies. But, a 26-meter watch tower and some solar energy
generators will be built this year to meet the station's needs.
