in Japan overwhelmed the Australian dollar Monday, causing it to
close almost three quarters of a U.S. cent lower.
</P>
<P>
At the end of trading in Sydney the local currency was buying
61.20 U.S. cents from 61.92 on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The news on Friday that Keizo Obuchi had won the race to be
leader of the Japanese Liberal Democratic Party (LDP) did little
to placate market participants.
</P>
<P>
Movements in the U.S. dollar/Japanese yen exchange rate will
hinge on such news and likewise the fate of the Australian dollar.
</P>
