<HEADLINE> Kuala Lumpur Stocks Close Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, July 27 (Xinhua) -- Share prices on the Kuala
Lumpur Stock Exchange closed lower in thin trading Monday due to
persistent selling, especially on key bluechips.
</P>
<P>
At the close, the 100-quality stock Composite Index dipped
10.36 points, or 2.48 percent, to 408.04, the all-share Emas Index
lost 2.11 points to 103.87, the Industrial Index down 2.60 points
to 856.66 and the Second Board Index closed lower by 0.63 of a
point to 90.50.
</P>
<P>
Losers led gainers by 389 to 140 with 152 counters unchanged,
241 counters untraded and 37 counters suspended.
</P>
<P>
The day's turnover dropped to 80.815 million shares valued at
136.984 million ringgit (about 33.168 million U.S. dollars) from
125.447 million shares worth 190.918 million ringgit (about 46.227
million U.S. dollars) on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The main board turnover declined to 77.726 million shares
valued at 133.114 million ringgit (about 32.23 million U.S.
dollars) from 122.387 million shares worth 186.652 million ringgit
(about 45.194 million U.S. dollars) on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The second board turnover increased slightly to 3.089 million
shares valued at 3.870 million ringgit (about 0.937 million U.S.
dollars) from last Friday's 3.060 million valued at 4.267 million
ringgit (about 1.033 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Off market deals increased to 5.255 million shares valued at
15.625 million ringgit (about 3.783 million U.S. dollars) from
1.736 million shares worth 2.524 million ringgit (about 0.611
million U.S. dollars) on Friday.
</P>
<P>
On a sectoral basis, consumer products accounted for 3.830
million shares traded on the main board, industrial products 2.999
million shares, construction 6.6 million shares, trading/services
26.922 million shares, infrastructure 694,000 shares, finance
18.884 million shares, hotels 201,000 shares, properties 7.365
million shares, plantation 1.691 million shares, mining 329,000
shares, trusts 55,000 shares, closed/fund 73,000 shares and loans
8.082 million shares. 
</P>
