<BODY>
<HEADLINE> EU Proposes R&AMP;D Association With Candidate Countries </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, July 27 (Xinhua) -- The European Commission requested
authorization from the Council of Ministers of European Union (EU)
on Monday to negotiate the association of candidate countries with
its research and development (R&AMP;D) programs.
</P>
<P>
Associated candidate countries for EU membership will
contribute to the budget of the R&AMP;D programs and in return
participate in the programs on an equal footing with EU member
states. They will enjoy basically the same conditions especially
with regard to funding.
</P>
<P>
Once approval has been obtained from the Council of Ministers,
the commission, the executive body of the 15-nation European
Union, will negotiate association with each of the 11 candidate
countries.
</P>
<P>
The candidate countries include 10 central and eastern European
countries and Cyprus. The European Union has invited Poland,
Hungary, the Czech Republic, Romania, Slovenia and Cyprus to start
accession talks.
</P>
<P>
Bulgaria, Estonia, Latvia, Lithuania and Slovakia are also
applying for EU membership.
</P>
<P>
All the 11 candidate countries have formally informed the
European Commission that they wish association in the R&AMP;D
programs, known as the fifth Framework for Research, Technological
Development and Demonstration for the period between 1998 and 2002.
</P>
<P>
However, commission officials fear the financial contribution
required from the candidate countries could present some
difficulties, though the candidate countries will be offered a
reduction in their contribution in the early years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
