<HEADLINE> 19 Killed in Bus Collision in South Africa </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, July 27 (Xinhua) -- Nineteen people were killed
and 65 others injured Sunday night when a bus collided with a
truck in South Africa's North-West province, South African Press
Association (SAPA) reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
Sixteen people died at the scene, including two children, and
another three died later in hospital, according to SAPA.
</P>
<P>
The 65 injured passengers were taken to two nearby hospitals.
</P>
<P>
The bus, carrying 84 passengers, was traveling from Mafikeng,
capital of the province, to Rustenburg.
</P>
<P>
About 10 kilometers outside Zeerust the bus collided on a
curve in the road with a truck carrying a full load of wood. The
bus left the road and overturned.
</P>
<P>
Seven men, seven women and two children were found dead at the
scene of the collision.
</P>
<P>
Police were investigating culpable homicide charges, SAPA said.
</P>
</TEXT>
