<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Iran's New Interior Minister Vows to Safeguard </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, July 27 (Xinhua) -- Iran's new Interior Minister
Abdolvahed Mousavi Lari Monday vowed to safeguard the public
freedom, saying that freedom is the natural right of Iranian
people.
</P>
<P>
"Freedom is not the thing that the interior ministry can give
to the people, rather a natural right of the people," Lari said at
a sworn-in ceremony held in the interior ministry.
</P>
<P>
He said that the government and the interior ministry were
duty-bound to safeguard the people's right of freedom and prevent
any damage on that.
</P>
<P>
Lari also said his future policy would focus on political and
social development, security and prosperity of cities.
</P>
<P>
To achieve the goal, the interior ministry will encourage the
people's participation by creating necessary conditions and
circumstances in line with the country's constitution and laws, he
said.
</P>
<P>
The minister underlined the importance of security and
tranquillity in the country, noting that the interior ministry
would make use of all possibilities to maintain security and
tranquillity in the society.
</P>
<P>
All sects should respect each other's views and beliefs, and
learn to peacefully co-exist.
</P>
<P>
Lari, who is also vice president for legal and parliamentary
affairs, praised the sacked Tehran mayor Gholamhussein Karbaschi
for his hardworking for the country, expressed the hope that the
verdict on Karbaschi would not cause any negative impact on the
country's leadership.
</P>
<P>
Karbaschi was sentenced to five years in jail on graft charges
and banned from public office for 20 years.
</P>
<P>
At the ceremony where Karbaschi was also present, former
interior minister Abdollah Nouri said that the country's
administrators and managers should continue their efforts for the
country's progress.
</P>
<P>
Moderate Nouri was impeached by the conservative Majlis
(parliament) on June 21 on charges of issuing inflammatory
statements, using inexperienced managers and inability to maintain
law and order in the country.
</P>
<P>
However, Nouri was soon appointed Vice President for
Development and Social Affairs by moderate President Mohammad
Khatami, showing the president's determination to continue
political and social reforms in the country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
