<HEADLINE> UK to Double Aid to Mozambique: Official </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, July 27 (Xinhua) -- Great Britain will within months
increase its aid to Mozambique from the previous 33 million U.S.
Dollars to 49.5 million, a senior British official has said.
</P>
<P>
"We plan to double the aid to 66 million Dollars" in the
coming three years, said Clare Short, the visiting British
Secretary of State for International Development, the Noticias
daily reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
Ms. Short made the remarks Sunday when she was visiting the
central city of Quelimane.
</P>
<P>
The British secretary was quoted as noting that the projects
assisted by her government need additional funds.
</P>
<P>
"Britain will continue providing support to Mozambique until
we are sure that it can walk on its own feet," Short said, adding
that Britain will keep watching to see Maputo's various efforts
for development so as to help it build up the basis for
sustainable development.
</P>
<P>
However, Short stressed that what matters is not the provision
of money but how it is used, and used with transparency.
</P>
<P>
Britain used to offer 33 million Dollars in aid to Mozambique
each year for its development projects.
</P>
<P>
In central Zambezia Province, Short inspected British-assisted
projects in such fields as farming, land-mine removing, road
building and education. She also met local officials, leaders of
the non-governmental organizations and British citizens working
in the province.
</P>
<P>
Upon arrival here Wednesday, Short said the aim of her visit
is to review the bilateral relations between Mozambique and
Britain and open up new realms of cooperations between the two
nations.
</P>
<P>
During her stay here, she met with Mozambican President
Joaquim Chissano and held talks with Mozambican ministers
including the foreign minister. Short left for home Sunday.
</P>
</TEXT>
