<HEADLINE> Tanzania to Have New AIDS Information Center </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, July 27 (Xinhua) -- The Tanzanian AIDS Project
(TAP) will set up an information center in Moshi of northern
Kilimanjaro Region in an effort to increase people's awareness of
the deadly disease.
</P>
<P>
TAP project manager Aishi Kitomari said the center will
educate the public on AIDS and provide counseling services to
clients.
</P>
<P>
Kitomari said the center will be operated by an information
officer, according to a report by the Guardian Monday.
</P>
<P>
The project manager told the paper last week that people will
be invited to visit the center and learn knowledge about AIDS
through video shows, books, leaflets, pamphlets and journals.
</P>
<P>
The TAP has set up information centers in Dar es Salaam,
Morogoro, Iringa, Dodoma, Tabora, Shinyanga, Arusha and Tanga.
</P>
<P>
The project manager said that T-shirts, brochures, booklets,
calendars, posters, stickers and billboards will be made and
distributed by the center.
</P>
<P>
Tanzania is said to be leading in Africa with a high number of
HIV/AIDS victims, with millions of people infected with HIV, the
virus that causes AIDS. 
</P>
