<HEADLINE> New House Speaker Elected in Philippines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, July 27 (Xinhua) -- Representative Manuel Villar was
elected the new speaker of the House of Representatives of the
Philippines Monday with an overwhelming majority vote during the
opening of the 11th Congress.
</P>
<P>
Villar won the three-cornered battle on the new House
speakership with a sweeping 171 votes as against 39 votes for
Sonny Belmonte and 11 votes for Joker Arroyo out of the total 221
House members.
</P>
<P>
In his acceptance speech, the speaker-elect who belongs to the
ruling LAMP party, promised to introduce reforms in the House to
regain the lower house's "favorable image".
</P>
<P>
He noted that the new Congress faces the real enemies which
are "mass poverty, injustice, ignorance and despair." He said that
under his leadership, Congress will be projected as "a friend and
champion of all Filipinos."
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, in the 23-member Senate, ruling party's Marcelo
Fernan was elected the senate president.
</P>
<P>
Following his election to the top Senate post, Fernan promised
the Senate will pursue a pro-poor legislative program in support
of the Estrada government's agenda to improve the lives of the
poor. 
</P>
</TEXT>
