<HEADLINE> Six Arrested in Chechnya over Attempted Murder </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, July 27 (Xinhua) -- Six suspects were arrested in
Chechnya Sunday in connection with the attempted assassination of
Chechen President Aslan Maskhadov, the Itar-Tass news agency
reported from Grozny Monday.
</P>
<P>
Those who organized and executed the attack on Maskhadov
Thursday would be detected in the near future, Chechnya's
Prosecutor General Khavazh Serbiyev was quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
The Chechen president was slightly injured when a car packed
with explosives detonated as the presidential motorcade swept
past.
</P>
<P>
In the incident, a bodyguard was killed, another died later in
hospital and three others were badly injured.
</P>
<P>
Over the past 24 hours, a total of 122 people were detained in
Chechnya for curfew violations, said a spokesman for the Chechen
National Security Ministry.
</P>
<P>
Twelve people were detained for the same reason in Grozny,
including a Chechen parliament deputy, the spokesman added.
</P>
<P>
Chechen authorities are reportedly determined to impose strict
penalties on government officials violating the state of emergency
rule.
</P>
<P>
The state of emergency was declared by Maskhadov last month
after a group of gunmen tried to occupy the state television
center. 
</P>
