<HEADLINE> Official Delegation Heads for United States </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 27 (Xinhua) -- A Chinese delegation of local
officials left Beijing today for the United States to attend the
42nd annual meeting of Sister Cities International scheduled in
Miami later this month.
</P>
<P>
Han Yingxuan, chairman of the Qinghai Provincial Committee of
the Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC) is
leading the delegation. The delegation also includes Gao Shizhen,
vice-chairperson of the Tibet Autonomous Regional Committee of the
CPPCC, and a number of high-ranking officials from Beijing,
northeast China's Jilin province and various other cities.
</P>
<P>
The delegation members will meet with U.S. congressmen while in
Washington D.C. and will visit a number of other cities, including
New York and Los Angeles.
</P>
<P>
Former U.S. President Dwight Eisenhower initiated Sister Cities
International to help U.S. cities establish friendly ties with
cities throughout the world and promote people-to-people
understanding.
</P>
<P>
China and the United States have established 30 separate
friendship ties between provinces and states, in additon to 96
sister-city relationships.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
