<DOCNO> XIE19980727.0128 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Egypt Says Joint Peace Initiative Gains Support </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, July 27 (Xinhua) -- Egyptian Foreign Minister Amr Moussa
said Monday that a joint Egyptian-French initiative on holding an
international conference on the Mideast peace is gaining wide
support.
</P>
<P>
Moussa made the remark before flying to Paris for two days of
talks with his French counterpart Hubert Vedrine and other
officials to propel the Egyptian-French proposal.
</P>
<P>
Egyptian President Hosni Mubarak and French President Jacques
Chirac in May called for such a meeting to salvage the peace
process, which has been stalled on all tracks since the election
of Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu in May, 1996.
</P>
<P>
Moussa told reporters that there is an Arab and international
acceptance of the Egyptian-French overture as one of the available
options if the Palestinian-Israeli negotiations fail.
</P>
<P>
"Failure to achieve a concrete progress at the time being will
harm Arab interests," he said.
</P>
<P>
Palestinian and Israeli negotiators met last week for the first
time in months but were unable to reach an agreement on
outstanding issues, including a U.S. proposal of a further Israeli
withdrawal from 13.1 percent of the West Bank in return for the
Palestinian security guarantee.
</P>
<P>
These topics were discussed in the northern Egyptian city of
Alexandria Sunday by Mubarak and Syrian President Hafez Al-Assad
as well as the tripartite summit held recently in Cairo grouping
the Egyptian, Jordanian and Palestinian leaders, Moussa added.
</P>
<P>
Paris talks, he went on to say, will also touch on the impasse
in the Palestinian-Israeli talks.
</P>
<P>
Those questions will also be discussed by Arab and Islamic
countries in the Al Quds (Jerusalem) Committee of the Organization
of the Islamic Conference in Casablanca, Morocco, said Moussa who
will be among the foreign ministers at the sessions on July
29-30. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
