<DOCNO> XIE19980727.0129 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Circular Calls for Relieving Burdens on Farmers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 27 (Xinhua) -- A recent joint circular called for
effective efforts to relieve burdens on Chinese farmers in order
to ensure their enthusiasm for production and ensure this year's
output targets.
</P>
<P>
The joint circular issued by the General Office of the
Communist Party of China (CPC) Central Committee and the General
Office of the State Council pointed to the difficult tasks facing
reform and development during 1998, and underlined the necessity
for ensure increased agricultural output, raising the income of
farmers and ensuring stability in rural areas in order to fulfil
tasks for this year.
</P>
<P>
The circular also noted that a number of factors contributed to
the slow rise in the income level of farmers during the first half
of the year, and led to increasing burdens on farmers in some
areas.
</P>
<P>
It warned that unfavorable factors pose a threat to the smooth
implementation of various reform measures and safeguarding social
stability.
</P>
<P>
The CPC Central Committee and State Council called on different
localities to reduce burdens on farmers by strictly controlling
reductions of overall fees on farmers, eliminating the collection
of random fees and related measures to designed raise funds,
strictly limiting fines on farmers and strengthening management
over voluntary labor.
</P>
<P>
All localities were urged to strictly implement agricultural
taxation policies, refrain from limiting rural income by using
grain purchase funds for other purposes and reduce tax burdens of
farmers.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, the circular called on localities to reduce
nonproductive expenditures at the township and village levels,
strictly deal with violations of laws and regulations, and enhance
leadership over the work designed to reduce burdens on farmers.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
