<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Flood Situation Worsening in Anhui </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, July 27 (Xinhua) -- The flood situation along the
Yangtze River in east China's Anhui Province continues to worsen
and the provincial government has mobilized over a million people
to battle flooding.
</P>
<P>
The water level at the Anqing Hydrological Station hit 18.13
meters, or some 2.05 meters above the danger level, at 8 a.m. this
morning. The water level along the entire 400-km Anhui section of
the river has remained above the warning stage since June 26.
</P>
<P>
Torrential rains have caused heavy flooding in a
number of cities and counties, with more than 80,000 people
evacuated from affected areas in recent days.
</P>
<P>
Related areas have organized 3,700 flood relief teams and have
assigned thousands of tractors and pieces of heavy equipment to
the effort along with over 2,000 boats.
</P>
<P>
The provincial government has instructed leading officials at
all levels to remain at their posts to direct flood control and
relief efforts.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
