<HEADLINE> Former French Coach Bans Himself From Seeing Team </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, July 27 (Xinhua) -- Aime Jacquet, the former national
coach who helped France win the soccer World Cup two weeks ago,
said on Sunday that he would see his beloved team no more.
</P>
<P>
"I ban myself from approaching the team of France and from
having contact with whoever he is. This is the law of our trade,"
Agence France-Presse quoted him as saying during a meeting with
the inhabitants of a village in Haute-Savoie at the Swiss border.
</P>
<P>
He said that he did so in order to help his successor, who he sa
id would have a difficult time in taking over and would guide the
team to defend the title in the 2002 World Cup.
</P>
<P>
France defeated Brazil to win the trophy for their first time
in history.
</P>
<P>
Roger Lemerre, 30, who is a friend of Jacquet's, is expected to
be proclaimed the new coach of the French team on Monday.
</P>
<P>
"I think that he has a past, an experience, a real-life
experience. The experience he has with us can allow the French
team to continue this ascension," he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
