<HEADLINE> Sainz Wins New Zealand Rally </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WELLINGTON, July 27 (Xinhua) -- Spaniard Carlos Sainz became
the most successful auto rally driver in history when he claimed
the victory at the New Zealand Rally in Auckland, New Zealand, on
Monday.
</P>
<P>
The Toyota driver finished the 25-stage rally in three hours 54
minutes 57.1 seconds to capture his 22nd world rally championship
title, one more than Finn Juha Kankkunen.
</P>
<P>
Sainz's French teammate Didier Auriol finished second in 3:55.2.
</P>
<P>
"This win is both important and special for me," said Sainz, wh
o won the opening rally of the championship in Monte Carlo back in
January.
</P>
<P>
"To set a new record of World Rally Championship wins is very
nice, but it is just as important to score victory at this stage
in the championship." Sainz said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
