<HEADLINE> Australia Edges United States in Men's Eight </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, July 26 (Xinhua) -- The Australian team edged the
United States at the finish line to win the title of the men's
eight at the Under-23 Nations Cup rowing championships in
Ioannina, Greece, on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The Australians finished in a time of five minutes 53.97
seconds, only 0.63 seconds ahead of the Americans in the final.
</P>
<P>
The women's four gold medal also went to Australia in 6:40.26,
while the United States finished second 6.43 seconds behind.
</P>
<P>
Germany topped the overall standing with 63 points, while Italy
was second with 51 points and Australia third with 37. Host Greece
was sixth in the 31-team event with 18 points.
</P>
<P>
The two-day Nations Cup is designed as a development regatta.
The World Championships will be held from September 6-13 in
Cologne, Germany. 
</P>
