<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Central China Province to Improve Rural Power Grids </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, July 27 (Xinhua) -- Central China's Henan Province
will recover 7.02 billion yuan State Development Bank loan next
month for a project to develop low voltage power grids in rural
areas.
</P>
<P>
The province will begin by improving power grids rated 10
kilovolts and below in 30 counties, and plans to upgrade obsolete
electric facilities in 115 counties over the next three years.
</P>
<P>
Henan plans to install over 35 million meters of 10-kv and 50
million meters of 0.4-kv power lines.
</P>
<P>
Counties consume 45 percent of total power generated in the
province, with the per capita power consumption of rural residents
standing at only 53 percent of the national average due to
obsolete power generation equipment.
</P>
<P>
The improvements are expected to help meet the growing demand
for electricity in rural areas and promote further development of
rural economy. 
</P>
</TEXT>
