the ongoing Asian financial crisis, particularly the need for
Japan to expedite the implementation of its economic reform
measures, which, in the process, will improve the economy in
Southeast Asia.
</P>
<P>
They also expressed the hope that the general elections held
Sunday in Cambodia would be fair, free and credible and exchanged
views on regional crisis including the controversial nuclear tests
conducted by India and Pakistan.
</P>
<P>
Albright informed Siazon that U.S. President Bill Clinton is
looking forward to meeting with Philippine President Joseph
Estrada who assumed office on June 30 during the APEC (the
Asia-Pacific Economic Cooperation) meeting in Kuala Lumpur in
November.
</P>
<P>
Siazon was the chairman of a series of ASEAN annual events
being held in the Philippines.
</P>
<P>
Before his meeting with Albright, Siazon also met with Austrian
Vice Chancellor and Foreign Minister Wolfgang Schussel, Australian
Foreign Minister Alexander Downer and Japanese Foreign Minister
Keizo Obuchi. 
