<HEADLINE> Jiangsu Evacuates Residents on Yangtze Islands </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, July 27 (Xinhua) -- East China's Jiangsu Province has
introduced emergency measures to evacuate residents on Yangtze
River islands threatened by heavy flooding.
</P>
<P>
More than 2,700 people have already been evacuated, with
no reports of casualties in related operations. The province's
14 river islands have a total population of 370,000 people and
farmland covering cover 18,000 hectares.
</P>
<P>
Jiangsu sections of the Yangtze recorded a water flow rate of
78,900 cu.m./second on Sunday, with flood levels rising to the
danger levels on some islands.
</P>
<P>
Xinji Island in Jiangning County, an area home to 4,100
residents and 400 ha of farmland, will be the first island to bear
the brunt of the new flood and the county government has organized
a 3,000-member task force to patrol on the 14-km embankment on a
24 hour basis.
</P>
<P>
Two separate breaches in embankments on Shiye Island in Dantu
County have seriously threatened 14,000 island residents. The
local flood control headquarters has attempted to fill the
breaches with 300 felled trees and 900 tons of stone. Some 1,638
people, including elderly, infirmed and disabled individuals and
children have been to safe areas.  
</P>
</TEXT>
