<HEADLINE> 14 Killed in Road Accidents in Bangladesh </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, July 27 (Xinhua) -- At least 14 people were killed and
more than 65 others injured on Sunday in three road accidents in
Bangladesh, press reports here said on Monday.
</P>
<P>
In Manikganj, 50 kilometers northwest of here, at least seven
persons, in including three women, were killed and 35 others
injured when a Dhaka-bound overloaded passenger bus with 45
passengers aboard trying to overtake a rickshaw plunged into a
canal on the Dhaka-Aricha highway on Sunday morning.
</P>
<P>
The driver of the bus managed to flee, and the injured were now
under treatment at a local hospital, police were quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
In the northwestern Thakurgaon district, a truck carrying
cattle traders skidded off the road killing five people and
injuring 30 others.
</P>
<P>
Police and survivors said the Panchagarh-bound truck from
Bogra, 170 kilometers northwest of Dhaka, plunged into a roadside
ditch. Villagers rushed to the scene, rescued the injured and sent
them to hospitals, they said.
</P>
<P>
And in Madaripur, southwest Bangladesh, two persons including a
12-year-old boy were killed when a speeding truck knocked them
down Sunday afternoon, the reports said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
