<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Stocks Down 1.7 Percent at Midday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 27 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong stocks dropped 140.40
points, or 1.7 percent, to close the morning session at 8,117.06
Monday.
</P>
<P>
The key Hang Seng Index fell 73.38 points, or 0.89 percent, to
open at 8,184.08 in the morning. 
</P>
