<HEADLINE> Central Government Ships Emergency Relief Materials </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 27 (Xinhua) -- The first shipment of emergency
relief materials from the State Flood Control and Drought Relief
Headquarters (SFCDRH) has reached flooded areas along the Yangtze
River.
</P>
<P>
The materials were shipped from state warehouses in Zhengzhou,
capital of central China's Henan Province, and Nanning, capital of
south China's Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region.
</P>
<P>
Hunan Province, one of most severely affected areas in central
China, has received 400 rubber rafts, 800,000 plastic sandbags and
240,000 sq.m. of cloth, with an additional 300,000 plastic sandbags
going to Jiangxi Province.
</P>
<P>
An SFCDRH official noted that additional relief materials will
be sent to flooded areas in the near future. 
</P>
