<HEADLINE> U.S. Grab Gold in Women's Platform </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, July 26 (Xinhua) -- Laura Wilkinson of the United
States won the women's platform gold with 504.21 points at the
Goodwill Games here on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
She secured her win after gaining 67.20 points with a 5235D
(back 1-1/2 somersault and 2-1/2 twists) during the last round.
</P>
<P>
The lady waved her right hand to the spectators and said later,
"I'm just really excited. The crowd was great. They really pumped
me up."
</P>
<P>
Cai Yuyan, a 16-year-old Chinese girl from Guangdong, became a
silver medalist with 501.57 points, only 2.64 points behind Laura.
</P>
<P>
Cai has been a lot of competitions in the past two years and
snatched the platform silver at the 1998 FINA World Aquatic
Championships.
</P>
<P>
The third place was also taken by Chinese teenager Sang Xue, a
14-year-old who dropped from the second to ninth place during the
fifth round.
</P>
<P>
She managed to catch up in later rounds, with 80.19 points
during the seventh round and 70.20 during the last and the ninth
round.
</P>
<P>
Sang said, "I know that I could do better. I have been diving
very well during the practices. I feel really happy to get the
bronze medal, especially because it was my first time in an
international competition." 
</P>
</TEXT>
