<HEADLINE> Earthquake Hits Zhangbei County in North China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIANGZHUANG, July 27 (Xinhua) -- An earthquake measuring 4.6
on the Richter scale, hit Zhangbei County in North China's Hebei
Province at 09:16 (01:16 GMT) today, according to the China
Seismological Bureau.
</P>
<P>
The epicenter was located at 41.1 degrees north latitude and
114.5 degrees east longitude.
</P>
<P>
The tremor was one of aftershocks after Zhangbei was hit by a
strong earthquake occurred on January 10 which measured 6.2 on
the Richter scale.
</P>
<P>
The quake was slightly felt in Beijing, about 200 kilometers
east to the quake-stricken area. And so far no casualties or
damage were reported. No details are available. 
</P>
