<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Different Farming Methods Removing Poverty In Qinghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XINING, July 27 (Xinhua) -- Comprehensive farming has helped
over 800,000 farmers and herdsmen in the under-developed Qinghai
Province on the tough Qinghai-Tibet Plateau in northwest China.
</P>
<P>
The province has a large number of people living below the
poverty line because of relatively backward farming and animal
husbandry methods.
</P>
<P>
The province has had 4 massive comprehensive agricultural
development programs since 1989 to help the poverty relief
program, and 734 million yuan in special funds has been used for
102 comprehensive farming projects that have benefited 825,100
people from the Mongolian, Tibetan, Hui, and Sala ethnic groups.
</P>
<P>
They have also helped add 21,500 hectares of arable land,
transform 60,000 hectares of medium and low-yield fields, and
increase irrigated areas by 55,000 hectares.
</P>
<P>
The program has also added 9,700 hectares of forest, 13
reservoirs, and 4,000 kilometers of irrigation canals.
</P>
<P>
Last year, per capita net incomes of 825,100 people in
comprehensive farming development areas were from 1,200 to 2,000
yuan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
