<HEADLINE> Northeastern Chinese Province Improving Marine Economy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, July 27 (Xinhua) -- China's Liaoning Province is
paying more attention to the marine environment as part of its
marine economy strategy.
</P>
<P>
The maritime industry has become a new growth point of local
economic development and has grown 20 percent annually since 1985
and is expected to bring in 40 billion yuan this year.
</P>
<P>
But it is serverly affected by declining offshore fishery
resources and a deteriorating environment.
</P>
<P>
The province has increased no-fishing periods to two months and
expanded areas covered by them to protect fish resources.
</P>
<P>
The damage caused by the excessive offshore fishing is being
reversed and the flow of pollutants from local industrial
production has decreased with the growing use of
environment-friendly facilities.
</P>
<P>
The coastal city of Huludao spent about 300 million yuan on
environment protection over the past three years, or 11 percent of
local economic development spending.  
</P>
</TEXT>
