<HEADLINE> Private Economy Sound In Eastern Chinese Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, July 27 (Xinhua) -- An average of 3,000 private firms
are born in Jiangsu Province in eastern China each month, which
has put the province in the lead in its private economy.
</P>
<P>
Recent statistics show 1.4 million private enterprises in the
province by the end of June. It has been looking for ways to
support private firms in recent years, a provincial official says,
pointing to the loosening of restrictions on loans and encouraging
them to participate in restructuring state-owned enterprises.
</P>
<P>
He explains that the rapidly-developing private economy also
feeds back into society, for example, paying 2.28 billion yuan in
taxes in the first half of 1998 and providing some 108,000 jobs
for unemployed people during the six-month period. 
</P>
</TEXT>
