<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 0100 GMT, July 27 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN -- Iran said on Sunday that its improved missile
capability is not meant for a first strike against other countries
but rather solely for defense purposes.
</P>
<P>
"Iran reiterates its commitment to the conventions and
international treaties regarding weapons of mass destruction," the
official news agency IRNA quoted Foreign Ministry spokesman
Mahmoud Mohammadi as saying. (Iran-Missile)
</P>
<P>
-- --
</P>
<P>
NICOSIA -- The Cypriot government Sunday rejected a threat
issued by Turkish President Suleyman Demirel, saying the Cyprus
problem should be solved through peaceful means. (Cyprus-Demirel)
</P>
<P>
-- --
</P>
<P>
PARIS -- French Foreign Minister Hubert Vedrine will pay an
official visit to Iran in near future, said French Foreign
Ministry on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
French officials said that France is interested in the new
political orientation of Iranian President Mohammad Khatami and
the visit by Vedrine is aimed at testing the readiness of the
Iranian government to open up the country. (France-Iran-Visit)
</P>
<P>
-- - -
</P>
<P>
LONDON -- A pilot and two medics died on Sunday when an air
ambulance helicopter crashed into power lines in southern England,
police said.
</P>
<P>
There were no reports of any survivors after the helicopter
came down in woodland near the village of Burham, kent.
</P>
<P>
The air ambulance was on its way to a road accident when the
crew were told they were not needed. The helicopter crashed on its
way back to a local airfield, police said. (UK-Helicopter Crash)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
TEHRAN -- Iranian President Mohammad Khatami on Sunday came to
the defense of his close ally, the convicted former Tehran Mayor
Gholamhussein Karbaschi, and vowed to "take legal actions" to
protect his lieutenants.
</P>
<P>
According to Tehran Radio, Khatami made his first reaction to
the Thursday verdict and sentence on Karbaschi in a cabinet
meeting Sunday afternoon. Karbaschi's case was a serious setback
for Khatami's moderate government, which came to power last August.
</P>
<P>
Karbaschi was found by a public court guilty of corruption
charges, and was sentenced to five years in prison and barred from
holding public offices for 20 years. Karbaschi will appeal the
verdict. (BC-Iran-Khatami-Mayor Verdict) 
</P>
</TEXT>
